    <!-- From the Titanium Server Admin Guide -->
    <p>Hypervisors are the compents in HPE Helion OpenStack Carrier Grade that creates and runs
      virtual machines.</p>
    <p><image href="../../../media/CGH-2-hypervisors.png" width="600" id="image_fsm_cg5_ht"/></p>
    <p>To view charts for monitoring hypervisor resource usage on compute nodes:</p>
    <ol>
      <li><xref href="../Dashboard/CGH-2-User-Dashboard-launch.dita#topic1160c2udl">Launch the HPE Helion
          OpenStack Horizon Dashboard</xref>.</li>
      <li><xref href="../Dashboard/CGH-2-User-region-selector.dita#jow1432757989702">Select the
          appropriate region and project</xref>.</li>
      <li>Click the <b>Admin</b> dashboard, then the <b>System</b> panel, then the
          <b>Hypervisors</b> tab. </li>
    </ol>
    <p>For each hypervisor, the following information is displayed:</p>
    <p>
      <ul id="ul_xj2_hh5_ht">
        <li>CPU Type </li>
        <li>VCPUs (used) </li>
        <li>VCPUs (total) </li>
        <li>RAM (used) </li>
        <li>RAM (total) </li>
        <li>Storage (used) </li>
        <li>Storage (total) </li>
        <li>Instances </li>
        <li>Status</li>
      </ul>
    </p>
    <section>
      <title>Compute Hosts</title>
      <p>Click the <b>Compute Hosts</b> table to view information on the hosts.</p>
      <p><image href="../../../media/CGH-2-hypervisors-compute-host.png" width="600"
          id="image_kth_4j5_ht"/></p>
      <p>The following infromation appears for each host:</p>
      <p>
        <ul id="ul_ywt_sj5_ht">
          <li>Zone </li>
          <li>Status </li>
          <li>State </li>
          <li>Updated At </li>
          <li>Actions</li>
        </ul>
      </p>
    </section>
    <section>
      <title>Hypervisor Instances</title>
      <p>Click the name of a hypervisor to view instances associated with that hypervisor.</p>
      <p><image href="../../../media/CGH-2-hypervisors-servers.png" width="600"
          id="image_ldl_xh5_ht"/></p>
      <p>In the Hypervisor Instances list, click an instance to see <xref
          href="../Instances/CGH-2-User-Instance-Overview.dita#topic804c2uio">Instance Details</xref>.
      </p>
    </section>
